  "title": "Project Engineer",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Summary</strong></p><p>You will independently manage M&E projects by overseeing budget, planning, scheduling, and deliverables to ensure successful project completion. Lead cross-functional coordination among clients, project teams, and subcontractors to drive smooth implementation and timely progress.</p><p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Lead project planning and budgeting to deliver M&E projects within scope, schedule, and cost targets</li><li>Organize and facilitate meetings to coordinate stakeholders including clients, project teams, and subcontractors for seamless project execution</li><li>Prepare detailed method statements, risk assessments, progress reports, and technical submissions to support project compliance and quality</li><li>Manage on-site activities by arranging manpower and materials to meet project requirements and timelines</li><li>Issue RFQs and negotiate with suppliers to secure competitive pricing and reliable delivery schedules</li><li>Systematically manage engineering and project documentation to ensure accuracy and accessibility</li><li>Monitor project progress and certify completed work to support timely payment claims</li><li>Participate in tender preparation and develop technical proposals to support business development efforts</li><li>Lead and motivate the project team to perform work safely and efficiently</li><li>Execute other ad-hoc assignments as required to support project and organizational objectives</li></ul><p><strong>Required competencies and certifications</strong></p><ul><li>Recognized Diploma or Degree in Mechanical, Electrical, Civil, Chemical, or Environmental Engineering</li><li>Minimum 3 years of experience in the construction field</li><li>Ability to collaborate effectively with all levels of workforce</li><li>Excellent interpersonal and communication skills to engage stakeholders and drive project outcomes</li></ul>",
